Let $A$ be a ring and $I$ a proper ideal of $A$. Let $J$ be an ideal of $A$ and $K$ a subideal of $I$. Then $J\bowtie K$ is an ideal of $A\bowtie I$ if and only if $JI\subseteq K$.
\end{lemma}



\begin{proof}
The proof is straightforward and may be left to the reader.
\end{proof}



